# Passenger process control for cPanel "Setup Node.js App".
# Goal: keep the account to ONE Node instance so CloudLinux NPROC (which counts
# THREADS, ~13 per Node process) never saturates the 100-task limit.
# cPanel injects its own PassengerAppRoot / PassengerStartupFile block above this;
# these directives tune the pool. If the host disallows any line in .htaccess,
# ask support to set it at the vhost level instead.

PassengerMinInstances 1
PassengerMaxPoolSize 1
PassengerMaxRequestQueueSize 20

# Optional: recycle a worker after N requests so memory can't creep (keeps the
# single instance healthy without ever spawning a second one).
PassengerMaxRequests 2000
